"xv6-riscv" is a re-implementation of Dennis Ritchie's and Ken Thompson's Unix
Version 6 implemented for a modern RISC-V multiprocessor using ANSI C.

On top of refactoring, this repository contains the following improvements on top of xv6:
- Implemented kernel threads
- Added exceptions for null pointer dereferences
- Changed the protection bits of parts of the page table to be read-only
- Added a lottery scheduler for processes
- System call tracing
- Alarm system call which periodically alerts a process as it uses CPU time
- Read counts system call